**Fixed**
I created an array of my functions excluding the count property that meant I only counted if it was a method acceptable to the fluent interface
```python
def __getattribute__(self, name):
		methods = [&quot;select&quot;, &quot;update&quot;, &quot;insert&quot;, &quot;join&quot;, &quot;where&quot;, &quot;get&quot;, &quot;row&quot;, &quot;last&quot;, &quot;first&quot;, &quot;fetchAll&quot;, &quot;chunk&quot;, &quot;override&quot;, &quot;orderBy&quot;]
		if name in methods:
			self._count += 1
		return object.__getattribute__(self, name)
```

